  <static seed="107" source="Contrib/PCC/BasicMath/FractionApplication/MixedNumberAdditionWordProblems20.pg">
    <statement><p>To pave the road on Ellis Street, the crew used <m>5{{\frac{3}{5}}}</m> tons of cement on the first day, and used <m>3{{\frac{2}{3}}}</m> tons on the second day. How many tons of cement were used in all?</p>
<p><fillin characters="11" name="AnSwEr0001"/> tons of cement were used in all.</p>
</statement>
    <answer>
      <p>
        <m>9{\textstyle\frac{4}{15}}</m>
      </p>
    </answer>
    <solution><p>This problem is obviously an addition problem.</p>
<p>To add mixed number, we break each mixed number into an integer and a fraction, and then add up integers and fractions separately.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{\begin{aligned}[t]
5{{\frac{3}{5}}} + 3{{\frac{2}{3}}} 
      \amp = 5 + {{\frac{3}{5}}} + 3 + {{\frac{2}{3}}} \\
      \amp = 5 + 3 + {{\frac{3}{5}}} + {{\frac{2}{3}}} \\
      \amp = 8 + \frac{3 \cdot 3}{5 \cdot 3} + \frac{2 \cdot 5}{3 \cdot 5} \\
      \amp = 8 + \frac{9}{15} + \frac{10}{15} \\
      
      \amp = 8 + \frac{19}{15} \\
      \amp = 8 + {1{\textstyle\frac{4}{15}}} \\
      \amp = {9{\textstyle\frac{4}{15}}}
\end{aligned}
    }</m></p>
<p><m>{9{\textstyle\frac{4}{15}}}</m> tons of cement were used in all.</p>
</solution>
